<br>
The only 3 I've been able to think of off the top of my head are:<br>
Skybreaker (which I have)<br>
Willsapper<br>
Blade of Strategy (or whichever one's the red epic)<br>
<br>
So starting there, could some people offer comparisons on those 3?  How do they do holding aggro, are they best in any specific situations, are the other stats good enough to warrant getting them?  And what other weapons would I want to look at that aren't too far off?  I have no clue on what the weaponry situation is like in WToV/early NtoV, lower end Ssra (eg Rhaggs), or whatever else there might be aside from the three I mentioned.<br>
<br>
Any input and advice would be apprecieated.  Thank you in advance.<br>
 <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=137021">Baron Saurix Shizathir</a><br>
Myrmidon of Cabilis, 59th Rank<br>
<a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/bdreadstorm">A Dreadstorm Tank</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udvara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dvara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/16/02 2:09:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=144.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: High-end Warrior Weapon choices</span><hr size=1> Didnt you have a wavecrasher? Though 9 19 is a bit old world, the proc is still incredible agro.<br>
<br>
Willsapper would be my first choice of the 3 you posted.<br>
<br>
Weapons that debuff / slow &gt; weapons that proc DD Skybreaker is nice but 75 DD is same taunt as a Ykesha only quicker. Hrmmm but that 13 19 is sweet too. And pure Damage per second is a great agro generator too. <br>
<br>
The other night in PoG I was pulling agro off you from time to time unintentionally. I wasnt taunting, my offhand is slow at 13 24 but procs 80 Poison DD and 80 dot poison for 4 tics. Mobs hate anything that sticks to them more than a couple tics. Much more so than small DD procs, unless you add a stun component.<br>
<br>
All of your weapons are good Saurix, but im my opinion I would ditch the Skybreaker for a Willsapper. Thats just me though. Im sure there are plenty others that would say differently.<br>
<br>
The red epic is a great agro generator, no question there. <br>
<br>
Dont forget all of this will be moot with Planes of Power as you will likely see stuff that makes the insane luclin weapons look tame. God I hope thats the case hehe.<br>
<br>
Dvara <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udvara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dvara</A> at: 10/16/02 2:24:56 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukhallim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khallim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/16/02 2:38:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=144.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: High-end Warrior Weapon choices</span><hr size=1> Wavecrasher, right..  forgot about that one, I've been casually looking for one for a while to replace the ol Frosty..<br>
<br>
and at PoG I was only half-playing most of the time, was on my other computer too..  might've missed a few taunts/could have been closer to the mobs..  but that's a nice proc on your weapon, too.<br>
 <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=137021">Baron Saurix Shizathir</a><br>
Myrmidon of Cabilis, 59th Rank<br>
<a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/bdreadstorm">A Dreadstorm Tank</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1191<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/16/02 5:48:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=144.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> IMHO ..</span><hr size=1> .. after Willsapper and Wavecrasher, the only large upgrade for taunt you can find will be from Hategiver and other similar very high end Luclin weapons.  Other weapons with similar taunt to Will/Wave manage it mostly through better ratios.  Ordinary primal works quite well, too.  My lizard can sometimes pull agro off a willsapper or primal warior for a swing or two during xp, but I rarely have to FD to give it back.<br>
<br>
Your only real taunt problem even with Hategiver will be rogues.  I've seen rogues (dumb ones) spin Tunare and AoW even after a warrior with Hategiver has been on it exclusively for +120s.  They'll try to blame the warrior, but don't listen to 'em.  Everyone knows it's the rogues fault.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udvara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dvara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 186<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/16/02 6:12:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=144.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: IMHO ..</span><hr size=1> Yeah theres some much better weapons out there, but I figure Dreadstorm is not quite up to Vyzra the Exiled yet.<br>
<br>
Blasphemous Blade of the Exiled,<br>
Bloodfrenzy<br>
Hategiver<br>
<br>
All excellent weapons <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usarhea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarhea</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Slave to Dvara<br>Tits of Steel Admin</span><br>  Posts: 1892<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/18/02 10:19:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=144.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://sarshouse.homestead.com/files/images/sar.gif width=52 height=126></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: IMHO ..</span><hr size=1> *furiously takes notes* <p><center><b><a href="http://pub15.ezboard.com/bsarscorner">Sarhea Yigsawla</a></b><br><i>Another taste of the evil I breathe,<br>
Will level you completely.<br>Wandering warrior of <a href="http://pub135.ezboard.com/banathema48379">Anathemat</a></i>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=braellarth>Braellarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 297<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/24/02 7:21:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=144.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: IMHO ..</span><hr size=1> Hategiver = more than the sk highest 'bought' agro spell, so in other words the spell i use one cast to grab agro from you.... thats what that sword procs.<br>
<br>
Skybreaker = crap taunt (one of lowest out there)<br>
<br>
That hammer from 8th shawl is extreemly 'better' at agro than skybreaker, though no where close in stats.<br>
<br>
Not all dots 'are' good agro, you will just have to play around.<br>
<br>
Willsapper on the other hand is a tryed and tested wepon, Infestation from DN is an ok wepon (not in same league as willsapper) but better than frost and skybreaker.<br>
<br>
There are no good two handed wepons 'with' extra good taunt procs however.. not better than one handed combinations.<br>
<br>
Braellar<br>
